---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | Foxry"
  description="Terms of Service for Foxry's applications, plugins, and website."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="legal">
    <article class="container legal-body">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: May 2026</p>

      <section>
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the applications, plugins, and website
          provided by Foxry ("we," "us," or "our"). By accessing or using any of our services —
          including current products and any future services we may offer — you agree to be bound
          by these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Services</h2>
        <p>
          Foxry develops and publishes software services including Shopify apps, WordPress plugins,
          and related tools for online merchants. The specific features, functionality, and
          availability of each service may change over time.
        </p>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue any service or feature at any time,
          with or without notice.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Use of Services</h2>
        <p>You agree to use our services only for lawful purposes and in accordance with these Terms. Specifically:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>You will not use our services for any illegal or unauthorized purpose</li>
          <li>You will not attempt to interfere with or disrupt our services</li>
          <li>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account credentials</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Use of our Shopify apps requires an active Shopify account. Use of our WordPress plugins
          requires a self-hosted WordPress installation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Pricing and Payments</h2>
        <p>
          Pricing for each app or service is listed on its respective page in the Shopify App Store,
          WordPress.org, or our website. All payments for Shopify apps are processed through Shopify's
          billing system.
        </p>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to change pricing at any time. Free plans may be modified, limited, or
          discontinued at our discretion. We will make reasonable efforts to notify existing users
          before significant pricing changes take effect.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All intellectual property rights in our services — including software, design, content, and
          trademarks — are owned by Foxry. Your use of our services grants you a limited,
          non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the service for its intended purpose.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may not copy, modify, distribute, reverse engineer, or create derivative works based on
          our services without prior written consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are provided on an <strong>"as is"</strong> and <strong>"as available"</strong> basis,
          without warranties of any kind, either express or implied. We do not warrant that:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Our services will be uninterrupted, timely, secure, or error-free</li>
          <li>The data or analytics provided will be accurate or complete</li>
          <li>Our services will meet your specific requirements or expectations</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Foxry's total liability for any claims
          arising from your use of our services shall not exceed the amount you paid to us in the
          twelve (12) months preceding the claim.
        </p>
        <p>
          In no event shall Foxry be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
          punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of profits, data, or business
          opportunities, regardless of the cause of action.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes to Services</h2>
        <p>
          We may add, modify, or remove features, change pricing, or discontinue services at any time.
          For material changes that significantly affect your use, we will make reasonable efforts to
          provide advance notice through in-app notifications or email.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an
          updated revision date. Your continued use of our services after changes are posted
          constitutes your acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of Japan.
          Any disputes arising from or relating to these Terms or your use of our services shall be
          subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the Tokyo District Court as the court of first
          instance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:foxry.support@gmail.com">foxry.support@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal { padding: var(--section-py) 0; }

  .legal-body {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .legal-body h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-subtext);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .legal-body section {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-body p {
    color: var(--color-subtext);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  .legal-body p + p {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    list-style: disc;
  }

  .legal-body li {
    color: var(--color-subtext);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    margin-top: 0.375rem;
  }

  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .legal-body a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }
</style>
